sub_title: Acting Communications Lead for Trane Technologies EMEA
summary:
I am a (currently) Netherlands-based Irish citizen with over 20 years experience with a multinational, across all aspects of communications, communications management, Public Relations and communications writing. My experience covers: corporate, leadership, staff management, crisis and media as well as stakeholder and community evaluation. Creating and implementing strategic business-supporting plans for both internal and external communications (including speech, article writing ), stakeholder mapping and engagement, global project management, non-technical risk assessment and community engagement plan development. 

I also have wide experience in staff management (including multi-locational teams) and training, helping staff to identify their skills gaps and close them and have had the privilege of working with people from many different nations in many different countries.

I love writing (in fact it's one of my main hobbies). I also love working with people and being part of a team, either face to face or remotely.
